  "text": "## Kubernetes RBAC Verb Coverage Audit - Complete Findings\n\nThis audit identifies all Go source files that define the set of allowed RBAC verbs and validates how API handlers enforce these verb constraints throughout the Kubernetes codebase.\n\n### 1. Core Verb Definitions\n\n#### HTTP Method to Logical Verb Mapping\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` (lines 176-189)\n\nThe `toDiscoveryKubeVerb` map defines the authoritative mapping from HTTP methods to Kubernetes RBAC verbs:\n```go\nvar toDiscoveryKubeVerb = map[string]string{\n    \"CONNECT\":          \"\",\n    \"DELETE\":           \"delete\",\n    \"DELETECOLLECTION\": \"deletecollection\",\n    \"GET\":              \"get\",\n    \"LIST\":             \"list\",\n    \"PATCH\":            \"patch\",\n    \"POST\":             \"create\",\n    \"PROXY\":            \"proxy\",\n    \"PUT\":              \"update\",\n    \"WATCH\":            \"watch\",\n    \"WATCHLIST\":        \"watch\",\n}\n```\nThis defines the complete set of verb names used throughout the system: **get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection, proxy**.\n\n#### RBAC Bootstrap Policy Verb Sets\n**File:** `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go` (lines 36-44)\n\nDefines verb groupings used for RBAC policy generation:\n- `Write` = [\"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n- `ReadWrite` = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n- `Read` = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- `ReadUpdate` = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\nThese constants are used to generate bootstrap cluster roles and to validate escalation.\n\n#### Code Generator Supported Verbs\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen/generators/util/tags.go` (lines 39-58)\n\nDefines verbs supported by the client code generator:\n- `SupportedVerbs` = [\"create\", \"update\", \"updateStatus\", \"delete\", \"deleteCollection\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"patch\", \"apply\", \"applyStatus\"]\n- `ReadonlyVerbs` = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n\nThese control what client methods are generated for resource types.\n\n#### Kubectl Auth Can-I Verb Sets\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/kubectl/pkg/cmd/auth/cani.go` (lines 108-109)\n\nDefines the set of valid verbs for authorization checking:\n- `resourceVerbs` = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\", \"use\", \"bind\", \"impersonate\", \"*\", \"approve\", \"sign\", \"escalate\", \"attest\"]\n- `nonResourceURLVerbs` = [\"get\", \"put\", \"post\", \"head\", \"options\", \"delete\", \"patch\", \"*\"]\n\nThe resource verbs set includes the standard 8 verbs plus custom verbs (use, bind, impersonate, approve, sign, escalate, attest).\n\n#### API Type Constants\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1/types.go` (lines 28-40)\n\nDefines RBAC constant for the wildcard verb:\n- `VerbAll` = \"*\" (allows all verbs)\n\n### 2. REST Interface Enforcement Chain\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/rest/rest.go`\n\nDefines Go interfaces that enforce which verbs are supported. Any REST storage implementation must explicitly implement these interfaces to support the corresponding verb:\n\n1. **Lister** (line 125) → LIST verb\n2. **Getter** (line 136) → GET verb\n3. **GracefulDeleter** (line 170) → DELETE verb\n4. **CollectionDeleter** (line 191) → DELETECOLLECTION verb\n5. **Creater** (line 202) → POST/create verb\n6. **Updater** (line 264) → PUT/update verb\n7. **Patcher** (line 286) → PATCH verb (combines Getter + Updater)\n8. **Watcher** (line 293) → WATCH verb\n9. **Connecter** (line 334) → CONNECT verb\n10. **StandardStorage** (line 303) → Composite interface requiring Getter, Lister, CreaterUpdater, GracefulDeleter, CollectionDeleter, Watcher\n\n### 3. HTTP Route Installation and Verb Enforcement\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` (lines 333-594, 796-1081)\n\nThe `installResource` function uses Go type assertions to detect which verbs a storage implementation supports:\n\n```go\ncreater, isCreater := storage.(rest.Creater)\nlister, isLister := storage.(rest.Lister)\ngetter, isGetter := storage.(rest.Getter)\ngracefulDeleter, isGracefulDeleter := storage.(rest.GracefulDeleter)\nupdater, isUpdater := storage.(rest.Updater)\npatcher, isPatcher := storage.(rest.Patcher)\nwatcher, isWatcher := storage.(rest.Watcher)\n```\n\nThen, for each HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, DELETECOLLECTION, WATCH), routes are only registered if the corresponding interface is implemented. This ensures:\n\n1. **Type safety** - Only implemented verbs create HTTP routes\n2. **Discovery accuracy** - Only supported verbs appear in API discovery\n3. **Authorization consistency** - Authorization checks only validate verbs that have routes\n\n### 4. Verb Matching and Authorization\n\n**File:** `pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go` (lines 26-37)\n\nThe `VerbMatches` function checks if a request verb matches a policy rule:\n\n```go\nfunc VerbMatches(rule *rbacv1.PolicyRule, requestedVerb string) bool {\n    for _, ruleVerb := range rule.Verbs {\n        if ruleVerb == rbacv1.VerbAll { // \"*\"\n            return true\n        }\n        if ruleVerb == requestedVerb {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\nThis validates that the requested verb matches one of the allowed verbs in the policy rule.\n\n**File:** `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go` (lines 178-193)\n\nThe `RuleAllows` function checks if a rule authorizes a request by verifying verb matching among other constraints.\n\n### 5. Completeness Assessment\n\n**Core Standard Verbs (8):**\nThe audit confirms all 8 requested standard RBAC verbs are comprehensively defined and enforced:\n1. **get** - Mapped to HTTP GET, interface Getter, bootstrap Read\n2. **list** - Mapped to HTTP LIST, interface Lister, bootstrap Read\n3. **watch** - Mapped to HTTP WATCH/WATCHLIST, interface Watcher, bootstrap Read\n4. **create** - Mapped to HTTP POST, interface Creater, bootstrap Write\n5. **update** - Mapped to HTTP PUT, interface Updater, bootstrap Write\n6. **patch** - Mapped to HTTP PATCH, interface Patcher, bootstrap Write/ReadUpdate\n7. **delete** - Mapped to HTTP DELETE, interface GracefulDeleter, bootstrap Write\n8. **deletecollection** - Mapped to HTTP DELETECOLLECTION, interface CollectionDeleter, bootstrap Write\n\n**Additional Verbs:**\n- Custom verbs via client-gen: updateStatus, apply, applyStatus\n- Custom verbs in kubectl: use, bind, impersonate, approve, sign, escalate, attest\n- Wildcard verb: \"*\" (matches any verb)\n- Proxy verb: In HTTP to verb mapping but not in bootstrap policies\n\n### Enforcement Architecture\n\nThe Kubernetes RBAC verb enforcement uses a **multi-layer defense strategy**:\n\n1. **Interface Layer** (rest.go) - Go interfaces prevent implementation of unsupported verbs\n2. **Route Registration Layer** (installer.go) - Type assertions ensure only supported verbs create HTTP routes\n3. **Authorization Layer** (rbac.go, evaluation_helpers.go) - VerbMatches function validates verb authorization\n4. **Discovery Layer** (installer.go) - toDiscoveryKubeVerb ensures consistency between internal verbs and API discovery\n5. **Client Validation Layer** (cani.go) - Warns about unknown verbs during client operations\n\nThis layered approach prevents mismatches between API handlers and verb constraints - if a storage implementation doesn't implement an interface, the verb simply won't be available at all.\n\n### Files Defining Allowed Verbs Summary\n\n**Definitive Verb Sets:**\n1. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` - HTTP method to verb mapping (toDiscoveryKubeVerb) [AUTHORITATIVE]\n2. `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go` - RBAC bootstrap verb groupings\n3. `staging/src/k8s.io/kubectl/pkg/cmd/auth/cani.go` - kubectl validation verb sets\n4. `staging/src/k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen/generators/util/tags.go` - Code generator supported verbs\n5. `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1/types.go` - RBAC API constants (VerbAll wildcard)\n\n**Enforcement Points:**\n1. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/rest/rest.go` - REST interface definitions (10 interfaces)\n2. `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` - Route installation with type assertions\n3. `pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go` - VerbMatches authorization validation\n4. `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go` - RBAC authorization enforcement\n\n**Completeness:** All 8 requested standard RBAC verbs (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection) are comprehensively defined in multiple locations and enforced through multiple mechanisms. No gaps detected in the verb coverage audit."
